value.0: Maryanne is the highest-ranking priestess of Selune on Amia. She is young, but dedicated.

Value.value: Welcome. If you need anything at all, please do not hesitate to ask. *she smiles, and then dips her head and speaks a small blessing*

value.0: A priestess of Selune, Violet is a young and kind-hearted soul known for making soup for anyone who might otherwise go hungry.
A priestess of Selune, Jenny is a middle-aged widow who likes to tend to the moon herbs in the chapel. It is said she is the one who tutored young Holly Redwheel.

Jeremiah Fischer is a local priest of Selune, known for his love of animals.

((Job System Trainer))

Carrigan is a citizen of Moonpier in her late twenties who often visits the church. She came to the town after the Arcanum war, bringing two infants with her. It is known that her husband died in that war and that she was quite young when she had the twins, but small-town rumor suggests she might be getting rather close to Jeremiah Fischer of late.

Brenden is one of a set of twins. He is the quieter of the pair, usually found reading, or fishing with Almarie Redwheel down by the harbor. He is known for being shy and keeping to himself, but he is very polite when he comes out of his shell.

Value.value: Hello. *he speaks shyly, staying close to his mother*

value.0: Light weaponry is oft looked down upon by the masses as the tools of cowards and weaklings. A dagger cannot put fear in an opponent like a glistening long sword. At least, not until a group of thieves, assassins and other nightwalkers known as the Guild of the Red Moon started carrying light weaponry that could punch through plate smooth as silk and quietly as a whisper. The Sureforged, as they are now known, are a must have commodity for any respectable adventurer who prefers his slaughter silent.

Refined and pressed into a liquid, this belladonna extract is extremely potent compared to the raw herb.

You can easy use this in small doses and still have a more effective means than chewing a leave.
A member of the Moonpier Militia. He seems intent on his duties of protecting the town. His equipment appears to be of high grade, glowing softly with an internal light.

A tracker's dream come true - Spectral Vision. This helm is so highly prized by assassins and other sophisticates because there's no known recipe to replicate the polished crystalline lenses that amplifies the wearer's sight tenfold.

A priestess of Selune, Fran is an older woman known to be the grandmother of Valridian Redwheel and wife to Hollis Redwheel. She is quite kind, and loves to sing.

Value.value: *pauses in her humming and smiles* Hello, dear.

value.0: Helena is the youngest acolyte in the church. She likes to welcome guests and point them in the right direction.

Value.value: Welcome to the Moonbeam Chapel. Let me know if you need anything!

value.0:
A warm, friendly physician with a keen eye for detail, Julia is happy to impart her knowledge to others.

((Job System Trainer))
Nurse Cheri is a warm woman who has long assisted the Selunitese by making the healing supplies they use.

This man in his late thirties stands at six feet tall with raven black hair and blue eyes that keep a keen watch on his surroundings. His armor is adorned with symbols depicting his faith in Selune and his Holy Symbol is aways in plain view.

Alaric is the Commander of the Moonknights, an Order of warriors and divine servants of Selune. Sworn to fight and defend in her name, the Moonknights have become a beloved part of Moonpier.
This item is not for PC use. If you have somehow come into possession of this, please contact a DM to have it removed and do not use it.

Value.value: Mind yourself here. The Moonknights protect Moonpier.
*You activate the Passwall with your key.*

value.0: Let all on whom Selune's light falls be welcome if they desire. As the silver moon waxes and wanes, so too does life. Trust in Selune's radiance, and know that all love alive under her light shall know her blessing. Turn to the moon and she will be your true guide. Promote acceptance and tolerance. See all other beings as equals. Aid fellow Selunites as if they were your dearest friends.
